### SCRAPI Registration Request
### Per draft-ietf-scitt-scrapi, Section 2.1 (Submit Signed Statement)
###
### The body is the raw COSE_Sign1 envelope (signed-statement.cbor).
### A Transparency Service would receive this and:
###   1. Parse the COSE_Sign1 array
###   2. Validate the protected header (alg, content-type, kid, CWT claims)
###   3. Verify the ed25519 signature
###   4. Apply the registration policy (see ../registration-policy.md)
###   5. Log the entry and return an operation ID

POST /entries HTTP/1.1
Host: ts.example.com
Content-Type: application/cose
Accept: application/json

< ../cose-example/signed-statement.cbor
